    <meta name="twitter:title" content={metaTitle} />
    <meta name="twitter:description" content={metaDescription} />
    <meta name="twitter:image" content={ogImage} />
  </Fragment>

  <article class="article">
    <header class="article-head">
      <p class="article-date">June 19, 2023 · by vivek</p>
      <h1>The Importance of Inclusive Design in Automotive Industry</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="article-grid">
      <div class="article-body">
        <p>
          The automotive industry is constantly evolving, and one of the most important trends is the move towards
          inclusive design. Inclusive design is the practice of designing products and services that can be used by people
          of all abilities. This is important because it ensures that everyone has the opportunity to enjoy the benefits of
          transportation.
        </p>

        <h2>Why is Inclusive Design Important in the Automotive Industry?</h2>
        <p>
          There are many reasons why inclusive design is important in the automotive industry. First, it is the right thing
          to do. Everyone deserves to be able to use transportation, regardless of their ability. Second, inclusive design
          can make vehicles more appealing to a wider range of customers. This can lead to increased sales and profits for
          automakers. Third, inclusive design can help to improve safety. When vehicles are designed for everyone, they are
          less likely to have features that can pose a hazard to certain groups of people.
        </p>

        <h2>What are Some Examples of Inclusive Design in the Automotive Industry?</h2>
        <p>There are many examples of inclusive design in the automotive industry. Some of the most common include:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Accessible vehicles: These vehicles are designed for people with disabilities, and they typically include
            features such as wheelchair ramps, lifts, and hand controls.
          </li>
          <li>Large print controls: These controls are designed for people with vision impairments, and they make it easier to see the controls on the dashboard.</li>
          <li>Voice-activated controls: These controls are designed for people with limited mobility, and they allow people to control the vehicle using their voice.</li>
          <li>Wide entryways: These entryways make it easier for people with mobility impairments to get in and out of the vehicle.</li>
          <li>Adjustable seats: These seats can be adjusted to accommodate people of different heights and sizes.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>The Future of Inclusive Design in the Automotive Industry</h2>
        <p>
          The future of inclusive design in the automotive industry is bright. As technology continues to evolve, we can
          expect to see even more innovative and inclusive designs. For example, we may see vehicles that are equipped with
          artificial intelligence that can adapt to the needs of the driver or passenger. We may also see vehicles that are
          designed to be more accessible for people with disabilities.
        </p>

        <h2>Conclusion</h2>
        <p>
          Inclusive design is an important trend in the automotive industry. By designing vehicles that can be used by
          everyone, automakers can make transportation more accessible and enjoyable for people of all abilities.
        </p>
      </div>

